quran[399]{c,v,t}:
  51,31,"He said, “And what, O messengers, is your mission?”"
  51,32,"They said, “We have been sent to a people in sin"
  51,33,“And to bring on stones of clay
  51,34,"“Marked by your Lord, for those who trespass beyond bounds.”"
  51,35,Then We saved those believers who were there
  51,36,"But We did not find there any just muslim, except in one house"
  51,37,And We left there a sign for those who fear the terrible penalty
  51,38,"And in Moses was another sign. Behold, We sent him to Pharaoh with clear authority"
  51,39,"But Pharaoh turned back with his advisors and said, “A liar, or one possessed.”"
  51,40,"So We led him and his forces, and cast them into the sea, and the blame was his"
  51,41,"And the ‘Ad was another sign. Behold, We sent against them the devastating wind"
  51,42,It left nothing that it came up against. It reduced it to ruin
  51,43,"And the Thamud was another sign. Behold, they were told, “Enjoy yourselves for a little while.”"
  51,44,"But they rebelled against the command of their Lord. So the stunning noise seized them, even while they looked on"
  51,45,"Then they could not stand, nor could they help themselves"
  51,46,"So were the people of Noah before them, for they wickedly transgressed"
  51,47,"With power and skill did We construct the firmament, for it is We Who create the vastness of space"
  51,48,And We have spread out the earth. How excellently do We spread it out
  51,49,"And of everything We have created pairs, that you may receive instruction"
  51,50,"Then hasten to God. I am from Him a warner to you, clear and open"
  51,51,"And do not make an object of worship with God. I am from Him a warner to you, clear and open"
  51,52,"Similarly, no messenger came to the peoples before them, except that they said of him in like manner, “A deceiver, or one possessed.”"
  51,53,"Is this the legacy they have transmitted one to another? No, they are a people transgressing beyond bounds"
  51,54,So turn away from them. There will be no blame on you
  51,55,"But teach, for teaching benefits the believers"
  51,56,I only created jinn and humans so that they may worship Me
  51,57,"No sustenance do I require of them, nor do I require that they feed Me"
  51,58,"For God is He Who gives all sustenance. He is Lord, powerful, and steadfast forever"
  51,59,"For the wrongdoers, their portion is like the portion of their people of earlier generations. So do not let them ask Me to hasten that portion"
  51,60,Woe then to the unbelievers on account of their day. The day promised to them
  52,1,By the mountain
  52,2,By a decree inscribed
  52,3,In parchment unfolded
  52,4,By the much-frequented house
  52,5,By the canopy raised high
  52,6,And by the ocean that is filled
  52,7,Indeed the doom from your Lord will indeed come to pass
  52,8,There are none who can avert it
  52,9,On the day that the firmament will be in dreadful commotion
  52,10,And the mountains will fly near and far
  52,11,Then woe that day to those who treat truth as falsehood
  52,12,That play in shallow things
  52,13,"That day they will be thrust down to the fire of hell, irresistibly"
  52,14,"“This,” it will be said, “Is the fire that you used to deny"
  52,15,"“Is this then a fake, or is it you who do not see"
  52,16,"“Burn therein, for it is the same whether you bear it with patience or not. You will receive the reward of your deeds.”"
  52,17,"As for the righteous, they will be in gardens, and in happiness"
  52,18,Enjoying the bliss that their Lord has bestowed on them. And their Lord will deliver them from the penalty of the fire
  52,19,"Eat and drink for enjoyment and health, because of your deeds"
  52,20,"They will recline on thrones arranged in ranks, and We will join them to companions with beautiful eyes"
  52,21,"And those who believe and whose family follow them in faith, We will join them with their family, and We will not deprive them of any of their works, each person is responsible for their deeds"
  52,22,"And We will give them all fruit and meat, anything they desire"
  52,23,"There they will exchange, one with another, a cup free of nonsense, and free of harm"
  52,24,"Around them will be youthfulness, like pearls well guarded"
  52,25,"They will advance each other, engaging in mutual inquiry"
  52,26,"They will say, “Before, we were not without fear, because of our people"
  52,27,"“But God has been good to us, and has delivered us from the penalty of the scorching wind"
  52,28,"“Indeed we used to call on Him. Truly it is He, the Merciful Benefactor, the Merciful Redeemer.”"
  52,29,"Therefore proclaim His praises, for by the grace of your Lord, you are no oracle, nor are you one possessed"
  52,30,Or do they call you a poet? We await them with calamity in due time.”
  52,31,"Say, “Wait, I too will wait with you.”"
  52,32,"Is it that their mind leads them to this, or are they just a people transgressing beyond bounds"
  52,33,"Or do they say, “He fabricated the message?” No, they have no faith"
  52,34,"Let them produce a hadith like it, if they speak the truth"
  52,35,"Were they created of nothing, or did they create themselves"
  52,36,"Or did they create the heavens and the earth? No, they have no firm beliefs"
  52,37,"Or are the treasures of your Lord with them, or are they the managers"
  52,38,"Or have they a ladder, by which they can listen? Then let such a listener produce clear proof"
  52,39,Or has He only daughters and you have sons
  52,40,"Or is it that you ask for a reward, so that they are burdened with a load of debt"
  52,41,"Or is the unknown in their hands, and they write it down"
  52,42,Or do they plot and scheme? But those who defy God are themselves the subject of a plan
  52,43,"Or do they have a god other than God. Exalted is God, far above the things they associate with Him"
  52,44,"If they saw a piece of the sky falling, they would say, “Fog-clouds gathered in heaps.”"
  52,45,"So leave them alone until they encounter that day of theirs, when they will faint"
  52,46,"The day when their plotting will not avail them, and no help will be given to them"
  52,47,"And indeed, for those who do wrong, there is another punishment besides this, but most of them do not understand"
  52,48,"Now wait in patience, the command of your Lord, for indeed you are in Our Eyes, and glorify your Lord with praise while you stand forth"
  52,49,"And for part of the night praise Him, and at the retreat of the stars"
  53,1,By the star when it goes down
  53,2,Your companion is neither astray nor being misled
  53,3,Nor does he say anything of his own volition
  53,4,It is no less than inspiration sent down to him
  53,5,He was taught by one mighty in power
  53,6,"Endued with wisdom, for he appeared"
  53,7,While he was in the highest part of the horizon
  53,8,Then he approached and came closer
  53,9,And was at a distance of only two bow-lengths or nearer
  53,10,So God conveyed the inspiration to His servant which He meant to convey
  53,11,His heart in no way falsified that which he saw
  53,12,Will you then dispute with him concerning what he saw
  53,13,For indeed he saw him at a second descent
  53,14,Near the lotus-tree beyond which none may pass
  53,15,Near is the garden of abode
  53,16,"Behold, the lotus-tree was shrouded"
  53,17,"His sight never deviated, nor did it go wrong"
  53,18,"For truly he saw the signs of his Lord, the Greatest"
  53,19,Have you seen Lat and ‘Uzza
  53,20,"And another, the third, Manat"
  53,21,"What, for you the male, and for Him, the female"
  53,22,"Behold, that would indeed be a division unfair"
  53,23,"These are nothing but names which you have made up, you and your fathers, for which God has sent down no authority. They follow nothing but speculation, and what their own soul’s desire. Even though there has already come to them guidance from their Lord"
  53,24,"No, will human beings have everything they pursue"
  53,25,But it is to God that the end and the beginning belong
  53,26,"However many angels there are in the heavens, their intercession will avail them nothing, except after God has given permission to whom He pleases, and that they are acceptable to Him"
  53,27,"Those who do not believe in the hereafter, name the angels with female names"
  53,28,"But they cannot know. They follow nothing but speculation, and speculation avails nothing against truth"
  53,29,"Therefore turn away from those who turn away from Our message, and desire nothing but the life of the present"
  53,30,"That is as far as their knowledge will take them, indeed your Lord knows best those who stray from His path, and He knows best those who receive guidance"
  53,31,"Yes, to God belongs all that is in the heavens and on earth. He rewards those who do wrong, according to their deeds, and He rewards those who do right, with what is best"
  53,32,"Those who avoid great sins and shameful deeds, only falling into small faults, indeed your Lord is ample in forgiveness. He knows you well when He brings you out of the earth, and when you are hidden in your mothers’ wombs. Therefore do not justify yourselves. He knows best who it is that guards against harm"
  53,33,"See the one, who turns back"
  53,34,"Gives a little, then hardens"
  53,35,"What, have they knowledge of the unknown and can they see it"
  53,36,"No, is he not acquainted with what is in the Books of Moses"
  53,37,"And of Abraham, who fulfilled his engagements"
  53,38,"Namely, that no bearer of burdens can bear the burden of another"
  53,39,That human beings can have nothing but what they strive for
  53,40,That their striving will soon come into sight
  53,41,Then they will be rewarded with a reward complete
  53,42,That to your Lord is the final goal
  53,43,That it is He Who grants laughter and tears
  53,44,That it is He Who grants death and life
  53,45,"That He created in pairs, male and female"
  53,46,From a zygote when lodged in its place
  53,47,That He has promised a second creation
  53,48,That it is He Who gives wealth and satisfaction
  53,49,That He is the Lord of Sirius
  53,50,"And that it is He Who caused to perish, the ancient ‘Ad people"
  53,51,"And the Thamud, nor gave them a lease of perpetual life"
  53,52,"And before them, the people of Noah, because they were all most unjust and most insolent transgressors"
  53,53,And He caused to perish the overthrown cities
  53,54,And they have been covered up
  53,55,Then about which of the gifts of your Lord will you dispute
  53,56,"This is a warner, of the series of warners ahead of him"
  53,57,The Ever Approaching draws near
  53,58,None but God can remove it
  53,59,Do you then wonder at this recital
  53,60,And will you laugh and not weep
  53,61,Wasting your time in vanities
  53,62,"But fall down in prostration to God, in worship to Him"
  54,1,"The Hour is near, and the Moon is cleft asunder"
  54,2,"But if they see a sign, they turn away and say, “This is a mysterious illusion.”"
  54,3,"They reject it and follow their lusts, but every issue has its appointed time"
  54,4,There have already come to them recitals with which there is enough to check them
  54,5,"Perfect wisdom, but warners do not profit them"
  54,6,"Therefore, turn away from them. The day that the caller will call them to a terrible affair"
  54,7,"They will come forth, their eyes humbled from their graves, torpid like locusts scattered abroad"
  54,8,"Hastening with eyes transfixed towards the caller. “This is a trying day,” the unbelievers will say"
  54,9,"Before them the people of Noah rejected it. They rejected Our servant and said, “This one is possessed.” And he was driven out"
  54,10,"Then he called on his Lord, “I am one overcome, will You help me?”"
  54,11,"So We opened the gates of heaven, with water pouring out"
  54,12,"And We caused the earth to gush forth with springs, so the waters met and rose to the extent decreed"
  54,13,But We bore him on an ark made of broad planks and caulked with palm-fiber
  54,14,It floats under our eyes. A reward for one who had been rejected
  54,15,And We have left it as a sign. Then is there any who will receive advice
  54,16,But how was My penalty and My warning
  54,17,And We have indeed made the Quran intuitive. Then are there any who will receive advice
  54,18,The ‘Ad also rejected it. Then how was My penalty and My warnings
  54,19,"For We sent against them a furious wind, on a day of violent disaster"
  54,20,"Plucking out human beings, as if they were roots of palm trees torn up"
  54,21,"Yes, how was My penalty and My warning"
  54,22,And indeed We have made the Quran intuitive. Then will any experience it
  54,23,The Thamud rejected their warners
  54,24,"For they said, “What, a human being, one from among ourselves? Should we follow such a one? Truly we would then be in error, and in madness"
  54,25,"“Is it that the message is sent to him of all people among us? No, he is a liar, an insolent one.”"
  54,26,"They will know on the morrow, who is the liar, and the insolent one"
  54,27,"For We will send the she-camel as a trial for them. So watch them, and be patient"
  54,28,And tell them that the water is to be divided between them. Each one’s right to drink being brought forward
  54,29,"But they called to their companion, and he took a sword in hand, and hamstrung her"
  54,30,How was My penalty and My warning
  54,31,"For We sent against them a single mighty blast, and they became like the dry stubble used by one who pens livestock"
  54,32,And indeed We have made the Quran intuitive. Then will any experience it
  54,33,The people of Lot rejected the warning
  54,34,"We sent against them a violent tornado with showers of stones which caused them to perish, except Lot’s household. We delivered them by early dawn"
  54,35,As a grace from Us. This is how We reward those who give thanks
  54,36,"And Lot warned them of Our punishment, but they disputed about the warning"
  54,37,"And they even sought to abduct his guests, but We blinded their eyes. Now taste My punishment and My warning"
  54,38,Early in the morning an abiding punishment indeed seized them
  54,39,“So taste My punishment and My warning.”
  54,40,And indeed We have made the Quran intuitive. Then will any experience it
  54,41,Also to the people of Pharaoh came warners
  54,42,"The people rejected all of Our signs, but We seized them with a penalty from One Exalted in Power, able to carry out His will"
  54,43,Are your unbelievers better than they are? Or have you immunity in the sacred books
  54,44,"Or do they say, “We, acting together, can defend ourselves”"
  54,45,"Soon will their party be on the retreat, and they will show their backs"
  54,46,"No, the Hour is the time promised them, and that Hour will be more terrible and most bitter"
  54,47,"Truly those in sin are the ones straying in mind, and in madness"
  54,48,The day they will be dragged through the fire on their faces. Taste the touch of hell.”
  54,49,"Indeed, We have created all things in due proportion and measure"
  54,50,"And Our command is only a single act, like the blink of an eye"
  54,51,"And in the past, We have caused groups like you to perish. Then is there any who will receive advice"
  54,52,All that they do is noted in books
  54,53,"Every matter, small and great, is on record"
  54,54,"As for the righteous, they will be in the presence of gardens and rivers"
  54,55,"In an assembly of truth, in the presence of the Sovereign, Omnipotent"
  55,1,"God, the Merciful Benefactor"
  55,2,It is He Who has taught the Quran
  55,3,He has created the human being
  55,4,He has taught him speech
  55,5,The Sun and the Moon follow courses computed
  55,6,And the herbs and the trees both bow in adoration
  55,7,"And the firmament has He raised high, and He has established the balance"
  55,8,In order that you may not transgress the balance
  55,9,"So establish weight with justice, and do not fall short with balance"
  55,10,It is He Who has spread out the earth for His creatures
  55,11,Therein is fruit and date palms producing spathes
  55,12,"Also corn with leaves and stalk for fodder, and sweet-smelling plants"
  55,13,Then which of the favors of your Lord will you deny
  55,14,He created the human being from sounding clay like pottery
  55,15,And He created jinn from fire free of smoke
  55,16,Then which of the favors of your Lord will you deny
  55,17,Lord of the two Easts and Lord of the two Wests
  55,18,Then which of the favors of your Lord will you deny
  55,19,He has let free the two bodies of flowing water meeting together
  55,20,Between them is a barrier that they do not transgress
  55,21,Then which of the favors of your Lord will you deny
  55,22,Out of them come pearls and coral
  55,23,Then which of the favors of your Lord will you deny
  55,24,And His are the ships sailing smoothly through the seas lofty as mountains
  55,25,Then which of the favors of your Lord will you deny
  55,26,All that is on earth will perish
  55,27,"But will live forever is the Face of your Lord, Full of Majesty, Bounty, and Honor"
  55,28,Then which of the favors of your Lord will you deny
  55,29,Of Him seeks every creature in the heavens and on earth. Every day in splendor does He shine
  55,30,Then which of the favors of your Lord will you deny
  55,31,"Soon will We settle your affairs, O both you worlds"
  55,32,Then which of the favors of your Lord will you deny
  55,33,"O you assembly of jinns and humans. If you can pass beyond the zones of the heavens and the earth, then pass. But not without power will you be able to pass"
  55,34,Then which of the favors of your Lord will you deny
  55,35,"On you will be sent a flame of fire and smoke, no defense will you have"
  55,36,Then which of the favors of your Lord will you deny
  55,37,"When the sky is rent asunder, and it becomes red like ointment"
  55,38,Then which of the favors of your Lord will you deny
  55,39,On that day no question will be asked of human or jinn as to his harmful deeds
  55,40,Then which of the favors of your Lord will you deny
  55,41,"The wrong-doers will be known by their marks, and they will be seized by their hair and their feet"
  55,42,Then which of the favors of your Lord will you deny
  55,43,This is the hell which those who are corrupt deny
  55,44,In it and in boiling hot water which they will wander round
  55,45,Then which of the favors of your Lord will you deny
  55,46,"But for those who fear the time when they will stand before their Lord, there will be two gardens"
  55,47,Then which of the favors of your Lord will you deny
  55,48,Containing plants of all kind
  55,49,Then which of the favors of your Lord will you deny
  55,50,In them will be two flowing springs
  55,51,Then which of the favors of your Lord will you deny
  55,52,"In them will be fruits of every kind, two and two"
  55,53,Then which of the favors of your Lord will you deny
  55,54,"They will recline on carpets, whose inner linings will be of rich brocade. The fruit of the gardens will be near"
  55,55,Then which of the favors of your Lord will you deny
  55,56,"In them will be those who are chaste, restraining their glances, whom neither human nor jinn has touched before"
  55,57,Then which of the favors of your Lord will you deny
  55,58,Like unto rubies and coral
  55,59,Then which of the favors of your Lord will you deny
  55,60,"Is there any reward for good, other than good"
  55,61,Then which of the favors of your Lord will you deny
  55,62,"And besides these two, there are two other gardens"
  55,63,Then which of the favors of your Lord will you deny
  55,64,Dark-green in color
  55,65,Then which of the favors of your Lord will you deny
  55,66,In them will be two springs pouring forth water in continuous abundance
  55,67,Then which of the favors of your Lord will you deny
  55,68,"In them will be fruit, dates and pomegranates"
  55,69,Then which of the favors of your Lord will you deny
  55,70,"In them will be those good, and beautiful"
  55,71,Then which of the favors of your Lord will you deny
  55,72,"Companions subtle, in pavilions"
  55,73,Then which of the favors of your Lord will you deny
  55,74,Whom no human or jinn has touched before them
  55,75,Then which of the favors of your Lord will you deny
  55,76,Reclining on green cushions and rich carpets of beauty
  55,77,Then which of the favors of your Lord will you deny
  55,78,"Blessed is the name of your Lord, Full of Majesty, Bounty, and Honor"
  56,1,When the inevitable event comes to pass
  56,2,Then will no soul entertain falsehood concerning its coming
  56,3,"Many will it bring low, many will it exalt"
  56,4,When the earth will be shaken to its depths
  56,5,And the mountains will be crumbled to atoms
  56,6,Becoming dust scattered abroad
  56,7,And you will be sorted out into three classes
  56,8,"The companions of the right, what are the companions of the right"
  56,9,"And the companions of the left, what are the companions of the left"
  56,10,"And those foremost, will be foremost"
  56,11,These will be those nearest to God
  56,12,In gardens of bliss
  56,13,A number of people from those of the past
  56,14,And a few from those of later times
  56,15,On thrones encrusted
  56,16,"Reclining on them, facing each other"
  56,17,Around them will be youth of perpetual innocence
  56,18,"With goblets, bowls, and cups filled from clear-flowing fountains"
  56,19,"No after-ache will they receive from it, nor will they suffer intoxication"
  56,20,"And fruits, any they may select"
  56,21,"And the meat of fowl, any that they may desire"
  56,22,And companions with beautiful eyes
  56,23,Like pearls well guarded
  56,24,A reward for the deeds of their past
  56,25,"Neither frivolousness will they hear therein, nor any taint of harm"
  56,26,"Only the saying, “Peace, peace.”"
  56,27,"The companions of the right hand, what are the companions of the right hand"
  56,28,They will be among lotus trees without thorns
  56,29,Among Talh trees with flowers piled one above another
  56,30,In shade long extended
  56,31,By water flowing constantly
  56,32,And fruit in abundance
  56,33,"Whose season is not limited, nor prevented"
  56,34,"And on thrones, raised high"
  56,35,We have created their companions of a special creation
  56,36,And made them virgin - pure
  56,37,"Beloved, equal in age"
  56,38,For the companions of the right hand
  56,39,A number from those in the past
  56,40,And a number from those of later times
  56,41,"The companions of the left hand, who will be the companions of the left hand"
  56,42,They will be in the middle of a fierce blast of fire and in boiling water
  56,43,And in the shades of black smoke
  56,44,"Nothing to refresh, or to please them"
  56,45,"Because they were accustomed to indulging, before that, with their wealth"
  56,46,And insisted on great harm
  56,47,"And they used to say, “What, when we die and become dust and bones, will we then indeed be raised up again"
  56,48,“And our ancestors?”
  56,49,"Say, “Yes, those in the past and those of later times"
  56,50,"“All will certainly be gathered together, for the meeting appointed for a day well-known"
  56,51,"“Then will you truly, O you who go wrong by treating truth as falsehood"
  56,52,“You will surely taste of the Tree of Zaqqum
  56,53,“Then and there you will fill your insides
  56,54,“And drink boiling water on top of it
  56,55,“Indeed you will drink like thirsty camels.”
  56,56,Such will be their entertainment on the Day of Punishment
  56,57,It is We Who have created you. Why will you not witness the truth
  56,58,Do you then see that which you throw out
  56,59,"Is it you who create it, or are We the Creators"
  56,60,"We have decreed death for you, and We are not to be stopped–"
  56,61,"From changing your forms, and creating you in forms that you know not"
  56,62,And you certainly already know the first form of creation. Why then do you not praise Him
  56,63,Do you see the seed that you sow in the ground
  56,64,"Is it you who cause it to grow, or are We the cause"
  56,65,"Were it Our will, We could crumble it to dry powder, and you would be left in wonderment–"
  56,66,"Saying, “We are indeed left with debts"
  56,67,“Indeed we are shut out.”
  56,68,Do you see the water which you drink
  56,69,Do you bring it down from the cloud or do We
  56,70,"If it were Our will, We could make it salty. So why do you not give thanks"
  56,71,Do you see the fire which you kindle
  56,72,"Is it you who causes the tree to grow which feeds the fire, or do We cause it to grow"
  56,73,"We have made it a memorial, an article of comfort, and convenience for the denizens of deserts"
  56,74,"Then glorify with praises the name of your Lord, the Supreme"
  56,75,"Furthermore, I call to witness the setting of the stars"
  56,76,And that is indeed a mighty adjuration if you only knew
  56,77,That this is indeed a Quran most honorable
  56,78,In a book well guarded
  56,79,Which none will touch but those who are clean
  56,80,A revelation from the Guardian Evolver of all the systems of knowledge
  56,81,Is it such a message that you would hold in light esteem
  56,82,And have you made it your life to declare it false
  56,83,Then why do you not intervene when the soul reaches the throat
  56,84,But you just stand there looking on
  56,85,"But We are nearer to him than you, but you see not"
  56,86,"Then why do you not, if you are exempt from account"
  56,87,"Call back the soul, if you are truthful"
  56,88,Then if he is of those nearest to God
  56,89,"There is for him rest and satisfaction, and a garden of pleasure"
  56,90,And if he is of the companions of the right hand
  56,91,"Then for him is the salutation, “Peace be unto you,” from the companions of the right hand"
  56,92,"And if he is of those who treat truth as false, and who go wrong"
  56,93,For him is entertainment with boiling water
  56,94,And burning in hellfire
  56,95,"Indeed, this is the truth with certainty"
  56,96,"So glorify with praises the name of your Lord, the Supreme"
  57,1,"That which is in the heavens and on earth, let it declare the praises and glory of God, for He is the Exalted in Might, the Wise"
  57,2,"To Him belongs the control of the heavens and the earth. It is He Who gives life and death, and He has power over all things"
  57,3,"He is the First and the Last, the Evident and the Hidden, and He has full knowledge of all things"
  57,4,"He is the One Who created the heavens and the earth in six days, and is firmly established on the throne. He knows what enters within the earth, and what comes forth out of it, what comes down from heaven, and what mounts up to it, and He is with you wherever you are, and God sees well all that you do"
  57,5,"To Him is the control of the heavens and the earth, and all affairs are referred back to God"
  57,6,"He merges night into day, and He merges day into night, and He has full knowledge of the secrets of all hearts"
  57,7,"Believe in God and His messenger, and give out of that which He has made you inheritors. For those of you who believe and give, for them is a great reward"
  57,8,"What cause do you have that you should not believe in God? The messenger invites you to believe in your Lord, and has indeed taken your covenant, if you are people of faith"
  57,9,"He is the One Who sends to His servant clear signs, that He may lead you from the depths of darkness into the light. And indeed God is to you Most Kind and Merciful"
  57,10,"And what cause do you have that you should not give in the cause of God, for to God belong the origins of the heavens and the earth. Not equal among you are those who sacrificed and fought before the victory, and those who did so later. They are higher in rank than those who sacrificed and fought afterwards, but to all has God promised the best reward, and God is well acquainted with all that you do"
  57,11,"Who is he who will loan to God a handsome loan? For God will increase it abundantly to his credit, and he will have a gracious reward"
  57,12,"One day you will see of the believing men and the believing women, how their light runs forward before them and by their right hands. Good news for you this day, gardens beneath which rivers flow, to dwell therein forever. This is indeed the highest achievement.”"
  57,13,"One day the hypocrites, men and women, will say to the believers, “Wait for us. Let us borrow from your light.” It will be said, “Turn back behind you and seek a light.” So a wall will be put up between them, with a gate therein forever. Within it will be mercy inside and outside, and all throughout will be punishment"
  57,14,"Those without will call out, “Were we not with you?” The others will reply, “True, but you led yourselves into temptation, you looked forward but you doubted, and your desires deceived you, until there issued the command of God, and the Deceiver deceived you in respect to God"
  57,15,"“This day will no ransom be accepted of you, from those who rejected God.” Your abode is the fire. That is the proper place to claim you, and what a terrible place it is.”"
  57,16,"Has not the time arrived for the believers, that their hearts, with all humility, should engage in the remembrance of God and of the truth which has been revealed, and that they should not become like those to whom was given revelation? But long ages passed over them and their hearts grew hard. For many among them are rebellious transgressors"
  57,17,"Do you not know that God gives life to the earth after its death? We have already shown the signs plainly to you, that you may learn wisdom"
  57,18,"For those who give in charity, men and women, and loan to God a handsome loan, it will be increased abundantly, and they will have a noble reward"
  57,19,"And those who believe in God and His messengers, they are the sincere and the witnesses, in the eyes of their Lord. They will have their reward and their light. But those who reject God and deny Our signs, they are the companions of hellfire"
  57,20,"Know that the life of the present is but play and entertainment, pomp and boasting, and increasing for yourselves, wealth and children. Here is a similitude, the rain and the growth which it brings forth pleases the hearts of those who plant it, soon it withers, and you will see it grow yellow, then it becomes dry and crumbles away, but in the hereafter is a penalty severe, and forgiveness from God and His grace, and what is the life of the present but stuff of illusion"
  57,21,"And for those of you foremost, is forgiveness from your Lord, and a garden the width of heaven and earth, prepared for those who believe in God and His messengers. That is the grace of God which He bestows on whom He pleases, and God is the Lord of grace abounding"
  57,22,"No misfortune can happen on earth or in yourselves, except that it is recorded in a decree before We bring it into existence. That is truly easy for God"
  57,23,"In order that you may not despair over opportunities that missed you, nor exult over favors bestowed upon you, for God does not love any vain boaster"
  57,24,"Such people are greedy, and recommend greed to others. And if any turn back, indeed God is free of all needs, worthy of all praise"
  57,25,"We sent our messengers with clear signs, and sent down with them the Book and the balance, that humanity may stand up for justice. And We sent down iron, in which is great power, and many benefits for humanity, that God may make evident who it is who will help, even if unseen, Him and His messengers, for God is Full of Strength, Exalted in Might"
  57,26,"And We sent Noah and Abraham, and established in their line the prophetic office and revelation, and some of them were on right guidance, but many of them became rebellious transgressors"
  57,27,"Then in their footsteps, We followed them up with more of Our messengers. We sent after them Jesus the son of Mary, and bestowed on him the gospel, and We ordained in the hearts of those who followed him, compassion and mercy. But monasticism which they invented for themselves, We did not prescribe for them. We asked only the seeking for the grace of God, but that, they did not develop as they should have. Still We bestowed on those among them who believed, their reward, but many of them are rebellious transgressors"
  57,28,"O you who believe, be conscious of God, and believe in His messenger, and He will bestow on you a double portion of His mercy. He will provide for you a light, by which you will walk, and He will forgive you, for God is Oft-Forgiving, Mercifully Redeeming"
  57,29,"So the people of the Book may know that they have no power at all over the grace of God, that His grace is in His hand, to bestow on whomever He wills, for God is the Lord of grace abounding. 29 (End of Part)"